parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sticking Brake Calipers and Overheated Brake Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake calipers and overheated brake rotors can cause the brakes to stick, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
burning smell from the brakes
smoke from the wheels
and overheated brake rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
and the brakes fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster display can lead to a lack of critical information, such as gear selection, oil pressure, and low oil warnings, which can cause accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle or engine.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display is dim
flickering
or completely inoperable
making it difficult or impossible to read essential information
such as gear selection
oil pressure
and low oil warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission gear indicator can cause the driver to be unaware of the current gear, leading to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle or engine.
symptoms: The transmission gear indicator is not displaying the correct gear
or is not displaying any gear information
making it difficult for the driver to know whether the vehicle is in reverse
neutral
or drive.
